        <p class="govuk-body">
        From October 2026, all waste receivers must use the new digital waste tracking service to report their receipt of waste. 
      </p>

        <p class="govuk-body">To make sure you are ready, you must:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>register for a Defra account</li>
          <li>pay the annual service charge</li>
          <li>decide how you want to report your receipt of waste</li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="govuk-section-break govuk-section-break--l govuk-section-break">

        <!-- TBC -->

        <h2 id="Who-can-use-the-service" class="govuk-heading-m">
        Who can use the service
      </h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">You can use this service if you are:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>a waste receiver with one or more licensed or permitted sites</li>
          <li>a consultant or representative of a waste receiver</li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="govuk-section-break govuk-section-break--l govuk-section-break">

        <h2 id="How-to-register" class="govuk-heading-m">
        How to register
      </h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">You can use this service if you are:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
          <li>Sign in or create a Government Gateway or OneLogin account for your business or organisation.</li>
          <li>Use your business or organisation's Government Gateway or OneLogin ID to register for a Defra account.</li>
          <li>Enter the address, contact details and company registration number &#40;if it is a limited company&#41; of your business or organisation.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="govuk-warning-text">
          <span class="govuk-warning-text__icon" aria-hidden="true">!</span>
          <strong class="govuk-warning-text__text">
            <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">Warning</span>
              Do not use a personal Government Gateway account for this service. 
          </strong>
        </div>

        <hr class="govuk-section-break govuk-section-break--l govuk-section-break">

        <h2 id="How-to-send-your-data" class="govuk-heading-m">
        How to send your data
      </h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">There are two ways you can report your receipt of waste:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
          <li>Connecting your waste software up to our application programming interface &#40;API&#41;. </li>
          <li>Downloading and completing a spreadsheet.</li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="govuk-section-break govuk-section-break--l govuk-section-break">

        <h3 id="get-started" class="govuk-heading-s">
        API
      </h3>

        <p class="govuk-body">An API allows different software systems to connect to each other so they can exchange data.</p>

        <h3 id="get-started" class="govuk-heading-s">
        Connect your waste software to the API 
      </h3>

        <p class="govuk-body">You must have waste specific software that your software provider will need to connect to Defra's Receipt of Waste API.</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">There is more information for software providers in the <a href="#">API authentication guide</a>.</p>

        <h3 id="get-started" class="govuk-heading-s">
        Get an API code
      </h3>

        <p class="govuk-body">You will receive a unique API code for every waste receiver on your account.</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">Give this code to your software provider who will apply it to your waste movements.</p>

        <h3 id="get-started" class="govuk-heading-s">
        Spreadsheet 
      </h3>

        <p class="govuk-body">If you do not have the software needed to use the API, you can upload your data using Defra's Receipt of Waste spreadsheet.</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">For every receipt of waste, you will need to:</p>

        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
          <li>Download the spreadsheet template</li>
          <li>Complete the mandatory data fields</li>
          <li>Upload the completed spreadsheet</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="govuk-body">
          <a href="/layouts/Private-beta/MVP-Registration/V1/Scenario-3/WR2/next-activity-org-2" class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state">Download spreadsheet</a>
        </p>

        <hr class="govuk-section-break govuk-section-break--l govuk-section-break">

        <h2 id="Timeline-for-reporting" class="govuk-heading-m">
       Timeline for reporting
      </h2>

        <p class="govuk-body">You must report every receipt of waste. You have two working days from the day after receiving the waste to submit your report.</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">For example, if you receive the waste at 9.00am on Monday you must submit your receipt by the end of Wednesday.</p>

        <hr class="govuk-section-break govuk-section-break--l govuk-section-break">

        <h2 id="What-data-to-submit" class="govuk-heading-m">
        What data to submit
      </h2>

        <p class="govuk-body">When you report your receipt of waste, you must provide the following information:</p>

        <h3 id="get-started" class="govuk-heading-s">
        Your waste receiver's details 
      </h3>

        <p class="govuk-body">If you do not have the software needed to use the API, you can upload your data using Defra's Receipt of Waste spreadsheet.</p>

        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
          <li>API code &#40;if you are submitting your data automatically&#41;</li>
          <li>Permit or exemption number</li>
          <li>ddress and postcode of where the waste was received</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 id="get-started" class="govuk-heading-s">
        Carrier details
      </h3>

        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
          <li>Business name</li>
          <li>Registration number</li>
          <li>How the waste was transported &#40;for example by road or train&#41;</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 id="get-started" class="govuk-heading-s">
        Waste details
      </h3>

        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
          <li>Date and time you received the waste</li>
          <li>Description of the waste</li>
          <li>European Waste Catalogue &#40;EWC&#41; code</li>
          <li>Physical form of the waste &#40;for example gas or liquid&#41; </li>
          <li>Number and type of container &#40;if any&#41;</li>
          <li>Total weight</li>
          <li>Whether the waste contains persistent organic pollutants &#40;POPs&#41; </li>
          <li>Whether the waste contains any hazardous material</li>
          <li>Discovery or recovery code</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-2">
          <a href="#">Full list of the waste data requirements</a>
        </p>

        <hr class="govuk-section-break govuk-section-break--l govuk-section-break">

        <h2 id="Adding-other-waste-receivers-to-your-account" class="govuk-heading-m">
        Add other waste receivers to your account
      </h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">If you operate multiple businesses or organisations that receive waste &#40;for example a subsidiary business or partnership&#41;, you can add them all to the same account.</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">You will need to pay an annual service charge for each waste receiver you add.</p>

        <hr class="govuk-section-break govuk-section-break--l govuk-section-break">

        <h2 id="Pay-the-annual-service-charge" class="govuk-heading-m">
       Pay the annual service charge
      </h2>

        <p class="govuk-body">The charge is not due until October 2026 but will cost Â£26 per year for each waste receiver on your account.</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">The fee applies to the number of waste receivers on your account. It does not apply to the number of sites that waste receiver has.</p>

        <p class="govuk-body">You will need a debit or credit card to make your payment online.</p>

